  "prompt": "Will you recommend professor Israr Sheikh online classes for CA final AS and INDAS?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, I don't have access to specific reviews or detailed information about individual instructors like Professor Israr Sheikh. However, when considering online classes for CA final AS (Accounting Standards) and IND AS (Indian Accounting Standards), it's important to look for certain qualities and criteria in a professor and their courses:\n\n1. **Qualifications and Experience**: Ensure the professor has relevant qualifications and significant experience in teaching CA final subjects. Look for any professional certifications and years of teaching experience.\n\n2. **Student Reviews and Testimonials**: Check online reviews and testimonials from previous students. Platforms such as LinkedIn, educational forums, and social media can provide insights into the effectiveness of the classes.\n\n3. **Course Content**: Review the syllabus and course content to ensure it covers all necessary topics comprehensively. The curriculum should be updated and aligned with the latest standards and exam patterns.\n\n4. **Teaching Style**: Different students have different learning preferences. Some may prefer a more interactive style, while others may benefit from detailed lectures. If possible, try to watch sample lectures or demo classes.\n\n5. **Availability of Study Material**: Good online classes should provide comprehensive study material, including notes, practice questions, and mock tests.\n\n6. **Support and Doubt Resolution**: Check if the professor offers support for doubt resolution, either through live sessions, chat support, or email.\n\n7. **Success Rate**: Look for statistics or information on the success rate of students who have taken the classes. High pass rates can be an indicator of effective teaching.\n\nIf Professor Israr Sheikh meets these criteria based on your research, then his classes could be a good choice for you. Always cross-reference multiple sources and, if possible, speak to current or former students to get a well-rounded perspective.",
